00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,400
and the various reference frames

192
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,400
that might be moving along the x-axis

193
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,400
alright, here's

194
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:02,400
here's time vertically

195
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,400
here's space horizontally

196
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:08,400
physicists always draw space horizontally

197
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,400
and time vertically

