01:07:57,240 --> 01:07:59,240
x prime is equal to zero.

1360
01:07:59,240 --> 01:08:01,240
It's my origin of coordinates.

1361
01:08:01,240 --> 01:08:02,240
Okay.

1362
01:08:02,240 --> 01:08:08,240
Now let's come to this

1363
01:08:08,240 --> 01:08:10,240
transformation law here

1364
01:08:10,240 --> 01:08:12,240
and see if we can spot

1365
01:08:12,240 --> 01:08:14,240
how to identify vt.

1366
01:08:14,240 --> 01:08:19,240
Well, x prime equals zero.

1367
01:08:19,240 --> 01:08:21,240
That's this trajectory moving

1368
01:08:21,240 --> 01:08:24,240
at an angle with a velocity v.

1369
01:08:24,240 --> 01:08:27,240
x prime equals zero is the same

1370
01:08:27,240 --> 01:08:32,240
as saying x cosh omega

1371
01:08:32,240 --> 01:08:38,240
equals t sinh omega.

1372
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:40,240
x prime equals zero.

1373
01:08:40,240 --> 01:08:42,240
Set this side equal to zero.

1374
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:43,240
And that says that

1375
01:08:43,240 --> 01:08:48,240
x cosh omega equals t sinh omega.

1376
01:08:48,240 --> 01:08:49,240
All right.

1377
01:08:49,240 --> 01:08:50,240
So whatever the connection

1378
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:52,240
between velocity and omega is,

1379
01:08:52,240 --> 01:08:54,240
it must be such that

1380
01:08:54,240 --> 01:08:56,240
when x prime is equal to zero,

1381
01:08:56,240 --> 01:09:00,240
x cosh omega equals t sinh omega.

1382
01:09:00,240 --> 01:09:03,240
Well, let's look at that equation.

1383
01:09:03,240 --> 01:09:06,240
It also says that x is equal to

1384
01:09:06,240 --> 01:09:12,240
sinh omega over cosh omega times t.

1385
01:09:12,240 --> 01:09:19,240
Well, that's interesting

1386
01:09:19,240 --> 01:09:21,240
because it's also supposed to be

1387
01:09:21,240 --> 01:09:25,240
equivalent to x equals vt.

1388
01:09:25,240 --> 01:09:27,240
Now I know exactly how to identify

1389
01:09:27,240 --> 01:09:29,240
what the velocity is

1390
01:09:29,240 --> 01:09:31,240
as a function of omega.

1391
01:09:31,240 --> 01:09:34,240
The velocity of the moving transformation,

1392
01:09:34,240 --> 01:09:36,240
the moving coordinate system,

1393
01:09:36,240 --> 01:09:40,240
must just be sinh omega over cosh omega.

1394
01:09:40,240 --> 01:09:41,240
Okay?

1395
01:09:41,240 --> 01:09:43,240
That's the only way

1396
01:09:43,240 --> 01:09:45,240
these two equations can be the same.

1397
01:09:45,240 --> 01:09:47,240
x equals vt.

1398
01:09:47,240 --> 01:09:50,240
x equals sinh omega over cosh omega times t.

1399
01:09:50,240 --> 01:09:51,240
So now we know it.

1400
01:09:51,240 --> 01:09:52,240
We know what the relationship

1401
01:09:52,240 --> 01:09:55,240
between velocity and omega is.

1402
01:09:55,240 --> 01:09:57,240
Write it down.

1403
01:09:57,240 --> 01:10:00,240
The velocity of the moving frame.

1404
01:10:00,240 --> 01:10:01,240
Now this is not the velocity of light.

1405
01:10:01,240 --> 01:10:07,240
It's just the velocity of the moving frame

1406
01:10:07,240 --> 01:10:09,240
must just be sinh omega

1407
01:10:09,240 --> 01:10:12,240
over cosh omega.

1408
01:10:12,240 --> 01:10:17,240
Well, actually I want to invert this relationship.

1409
01:10:17,240 --> 01:10:20,240
I want to find sinh and cosh omega

1410
01:10:20,240 --> 01:10:22,240
in terms of the velocity.

1411
01:10:22,240 --> 01:10:25,240
I want to rewrite these Lorentz transformations.

1412
01:10:25,240 --> 01:10:26,240
Where are they?

1413
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:30,240
I want to rewrite these Lorentz transformations

1414
01:10:30,240 --> 01:10:33,240
in terms of the velocity.

1415
01:10:33,240 --> 01:10:35,240
That's the familiar form

1416
01:10:35,240 --> 01:10:37,240
in which you learn about it

1417
01:10:37,240 --> 01:10:40,240
in elementary relativity books.

1418
01:10:40,240 --> 01:10:43,240
x prime is equal to something with velocities in it.

1419
01:10:43,240 --> 01:10:45,240
To exhibit that,

1420
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:48,240
all we have to do is to find sinh and cosh omega

1421
01:10:48,240 --> 01:10:50,240
in terms of the velocity.

1422
01:10:50,240 --> 01:10:52,240
That's not very hard.

1423
01:10:52,240 --> 01:10:54,240
Let's work it out.

1424
01:10:54,240 --> 01:11:00,240
The first step is to square it.

1425
01:11:00,240 --> 01:11:03,240
And to write v squared is equal to

1426
01:11:03,240 --> 01:11:06,240
sinh omega squared

1427
01:11:06,240 --> 01:11:08,240
over cosh omega squared.

1428
01:11:08,240 --> 01:11:10,240
That was easy.

1429
01:11:10,240 --> 01:11:15,240
Next, I'm going to get rid of sinh omega squared

1430
01:11:15,240 --> 01:11:16,240
and substitute.

1431
01:11:16,240 --> 01:11:17,240
Where is it?

1432
01:11:17,240 --> 01:11:20,240
I lost it.

1433
01:11:20,240 --> 01:11:24,240
One is equal to cosh omega squared

1434
01:11:24,240 --> 01:11:30,240
minus sinh omega squared.

1435
01:11:30,240 --> 01:11:31,240
All right.

1436
01:11:31,240 --> 01:11:33,240
So wherever I see sinh omega squared,

1437
01:11:33,240 --> 01:11:35,240
I can substitute from here.

1438
01:11:35,240 --> 01:11:40,240
Namely, cosh squared omega minus one

1439
01:11:40,240 --> 01:11:44,240
is equal to sinh squared omega.

1440
01:11:44,240 --> 01:11:46,240
So here we are.

1441
01:11:46,240 --> 01:11:48,240
This is just equal to

1442
01:11:48,240 --> 01:11:51,240
cosh of omega squared

1443
01:11:51,240 --> 01:11:53,240
minus one

1444
01:11:53,240 --> 01:11:59,240
divided by cosh of omega squared.

1445
01:11:59,240 --> 01:12:02,240
Or,

1446
01:12:02,240 --> 01:12:04,240
let's multiply by,

1447
01:12:04,240 --> 01:12:07,240
what I want to do is solve for cosh omega

1448
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:09,240
in terms of velocity.

1449
01:12:09,240 --> 01:12:12,240
I want to get rid of all these coshes and sinhs of omega

1450
01:12:12,240 --> 01:12:14,240
and rewrite it in terms of velocity.

1451
01:12:14,240 --> 01:12:18,240
So first multiply by cosh omega

1452
01:12:18,240 --> 01:12:20,240
squared.

1453
01:12:20,240 --> 01:12:23,240
We have cosh squared omega

1454
01:12:23,240 --> 01:12:25,240
times v squared

1455
01:12:25,240 --> 01:12:29,240
equals cosh squared omega minus one.

1456
01:12:29,240 --> 01:12:35,240
Or,

1457
01:12:35,240 --> 01:12:38,240
it looks to me like this is cosh

1458
01:12:38,240 --> 01:12:40,240
squared omega

1459
01:12:40,240 --> 01:12:43,240
times one minus v squared

1460
01:12:43,240 --> 01:12:45,240
equals one.

1461
01:12:45,240 --> 01:12:49,240
What I've done is transpose,

1462
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:57,240
yeah,

1463
01:12:57,240 --> 01:13:00,240
cosh squared times v squared

1464
01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:02,240
minus cosh squared itself.

1465
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:06,240
That gives you cosh squared one minus v squared

1466
01:13:06,240 --> 01:13:07,240
equals one.

1467
01:13:07,240 --> 01:13:09,240
Change the sign.

1468
01:13:09,240 --> 01:13:13,240
Can everybody see that the second line follows from the first?

1469
01:13:15,240 --> 01:13:17,240
I'll give you a second.

1470
01:13:17,240 --> 01:13:24,240
Put the one on the left-hand side and then put the v squared on the right-hand side.

1471
01:13:24,240 --> 01:13:25,240
Yeah.

1472
01:13:25,240 --> 01:13:26,240
Yeah.

1473
01:13:26,240 --> 01:13:27,240
It's clear.

1474
01:13:27,240 --> 01:13:28,240
Okay.

1475
01:13:28,240 --> 01:13:29,240
Finally,

1476
01:13:29,240 --> 01:13:30,240
we get

1477
01:13:30,240 --> 01:13:34,240
that cosh omega

1478
01:13:34,240 --> 01:13:38,240
is equal to one divided by one minus v squared,

1479
01:13:38,240 --> 01:13:43,240
but now I have to take the square root.

1480
01:13:43,240 --> 01:13:52,240
Cosh omega

1481
01:13:52,240 --> 01:13:54,240
divide by one minus v squared and then take the square root.

1482
01:13:54,240 --> 01:13:55,240
Okay.

1483
01:13:55,240 --> 01:13:58,240
And that gives you cosh omega.

1484
01:13:58,240 --> 01:14:03,240
Now, we've all seen these square roots of one minus v squared in relativity formulas.

1485
01:14:03,240 --> 01:14:04,240
Here's where it begins to come.

1486
01:14:04,240 --> 01:14:06,240
Here we begin to see it materializing.

1487
01:14:06,240 --> 01:14:08,240
What about sinh omega?

1488
01:14:08,240 --> 01:14:13,240
Let's also write down sinh omega.

1489
01:14:13,240 --> 01:14:15,240
Well, from here,

1490
01:14:15,240 --> 01:14:17,240
we see that sinh omega

1491
01:14:17,240 --> 01:14:20,240
is just equal to v times cosh omega.

1492
01:14:20,240 --> 01:14:21,240
This is easy.

1493
01:14:21,240 --> 01:14:24,240
Sinh omega equals v times cosh omega.

1494
01:14:24,240 --> 01:14:35,240
So, sinh omega is v divided by square root of one minus v squared.

1495
01:14:35,240 --> 01:14:40,240
Let's go back to these Lorentz transformations over here

1496
01:14:40,240 --> 01:14:43,240
and write them getting rid of the trigonometric functions,

1497
01:14:43,240 --> 01:14:46,240
the hyperbolic trigonometric functions,

1498
01:14:46,240 --> 01:14:50,240
and substituting good old familiar velocities.

1499
01:14:50,240 --> 01:14:53,240
Let's get rid of this

1500
01:14:53,240 --> 01:15:00,240
and substitute the good old ordinary velocities.

1501
01:15:00,240 --> 01:15:02,240
Okay, so we have here

1502
01:15:02,240 --> 01:15:07,240
x prime equals x times cosh omega

1503
01:15:07,240 --> 01:15:11,240
and that's divided by square root of one minus v squared.

1504
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:16,240
Then there's minus t times sinh omega,

1505
01:15:16,240 --> 01:15:21,240
which is v over the square root of one minus v squared.

1506
01:15:21,240 --> 01:15:22,240
If I put the two of them together,

1507
01:15:22,240 --> 01:15:25,240
and combine them over the same denominator,

1508
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:30,240
it's just x minus vt

1509
01:15:30,240 --> 01:15:34,240
divided by square root

1510
01:15:34,240 --> 01:15:39,240
of one minus v squared.

1511
01:15:39,240 --> 01:15:43,240
I think most of you have probably seen that before.

1512
01:15:43,240 --> 01:15:45,240
Maybe slightly different.

1513
01:15:45,240 --> 01:15:48,240
Let's clean it up a little bit.

1514
01:15:48,240 --> 01:15:50,240
x prime equals

1515
01:15:50,240 --> 01:15:53,240
x minus vt

1516
01:15:53,240 --> 01:15:57,240
divided by the square root of one minus v squared.

1517
01:15:57,240 --> 01:15:59,240
What about t prime?

1518
01:15:59,240 --> 01:16:05,240
t prime is equal to t

1519
01:16:05,240 --> 01:16:07,240
minus vx

1520
01:16:07,240 --> 01:16:11,240
over square root of one minus v squared.

1521
01:16:11,240 --> 01:16:15,240
t prime is equal to t times cosh,

1522
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:17,240
cosh is just one over square root,

1523
01:16:17,240 --> 01:16:20,240
and then x times sinh,

1524
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:22,240
that gives us the extra v.

1525
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:29,240
In other words, the formulas are more or less symmetrical.

1526
01:16:29,240 --> 01:16:31,240
And those are our good old Lorentz transformations.

1527
01:16:31,240 --> 01:16:34,240
Now what's missing is the speed of light.

1528
01:16:34,240 --> 01:16:36,240
Let's put back the speed of light.

1529
01:16:36,240 --> 01:16:41,240
To put back the speed of light is an exercise in dimensional analysis.

1530
01:16:41,240 --> 01:16:46,240
There's only one possible way the speed of light can fit into these equations.

1531
01:16:46,240 --> 01:16:50,240
They have to be modified so that they're dimensionally correct.

1532
01:16:50,240 --> 01:16:54,240
First of all, one is dimensionless.

1533
01:16:54,240 --> 01:16:56,240
It has no dimensions, it's just one.

1534
01:16:56,240 --> 01:16:59,240
Velocity is not dimensionless,

1535
01:16:59,240 --> 01:17:03,240
unless, of course, we use dimensionless notation for it.

1536
01:17:03,240 --> 01:17:08,240
But if velocity is measured in meters per second,

1537
01:17:08,240 --> 01:17:10,240
then it's not dimensionless.

1538
01:17:10,240 --> 01:17:12,240
How do we make v squared dimensionless?

1539
01:17:12,240 --> 01:17:14,240
We divide it by the square of the speed of light.

1540
01:17:14,240 --> 01:17:17,240
In other words, this v squared, which is here,

1541
01:17:17,240 --> 01:17:19,240
which has been defined

1542
01:17:19,240 --> 01:17:22,240
in units in which the speed of light is one,

1543
01:17:22,240 --> 01:17:27,240
has to be replaced by v squared over c squared.

1544
01:17:27,240 --> 01:17:30,240
Likewise over here.

1545
01:17:30,240 --> 01:17:33,240
v squared over c squared.

1546
01:17:33,240 --> 01:17:37,240
Now, velocity times time does have...

1547
01:17:37,240 --> 01:17:41,240
Notice, first of all, the left-hand side has units of length.

1548
01:17:41,240 --> 01:17:44,240
The right-hand side, this is dimensionless.

1549
01:17:44,240 --> 01:17:46,240
x has units of length,

1550
01:17:46,240 --> 01:17:49,240
but so does velocity times time.

1551
01:17:49,240 --> 01:17:51,240
So this is okay.

1552
01:17:51,240 --> 01:17:54,240
This is dimensionally consistent as it is.

1553
01:17:54,240 --> 01:17:55,240
But over here it's not.

1554
01:17:55,240 --> 01:17:57,240
The left-hand side has dimensions of time.

1555
01:17:57,240 --> 01:17:59,240
That's all right.

1556
01:17:59,240 --> 01:18:02,240
1 minus v squared over c squared, that's dimensionless.

1557
01:18:02,240 --> 01:18:04,240
This has units of time.

1558
01:18:04,240 --> 01:18:07,240
But what about velocity times x?

1559
01:18:07,240 --> 01:18:10,240
Velocity times x does not have units of time.

1560
01:18:10,240 --> 01:18:12,240
In order to give it units of time,

1561
01:18:12,240 --> 01:18:15,240
you have to divide it by c squared.

1562
01:18:15,240 --> 01:18:18,240
Okay, let's check that.

1563
01:18:18,240 --> 01:18:23,240
Velocity is length over time

1564
01:18:23,240 --> 01:18:25,240
times length

1565
01:18:25,240 --> 01:18:27,240
divided by c squared.

1566
01:18:27,240 --> 01:18:29,240
That's length squared...

1567
01:18:29,240 --> 01:18:32,240
Oh, it's correct.

1568
01:18:32,240 --> 01:18:37,240
It's correct.

1569
01:18:37,240 --> 01:18:40,240
All right, this is probably familiar to most of you

1570
01:18:40,240 --> 01:18:43,240
who've seen relativity once or twice before.

1571
01:18:43,240 --> 01:18:46,240
These are the equations relating

1572
01:18:46,240 --> 01:18:49,240
two different moving coordinate systems

1573
01:18:49,240 --> 01:18:51,240
moving relative to the x-axis.

1574
01:18:51,240 --> 01:18:53,240
But you see, the deep mathematics

1575
01:18:53,240 --> 01:18:56,240
or the mathematical structure of it

1576
01:18:56,240 --> 01:18:59,240
in many ways is best reflected

1577
01:18:59,240 --> 01:19:03,240
by this kind of hyperbolic geometry here.

1578
01:19:03,240 --> 01:19:08,240
And, you know, most physicists by now

1579
01:19:08,240 --> 01:19:12,240
never write down the Lorentz transformations

1580
01:19:12,240 --> 01:19:14,240
in this form.

1581
01:19:14,240 --> 01:19:16,240
Much more likely to write them

1582
01:19:16,240 --> 01:19:18,240
in this form.

1583
01:19:18,240 --> 01:19:20,240
Easier to manipulate.

1584
01:19:20,240 --> 01:19:22,240
Easier to use trigonometry

1585
01:19:22,240 --> 01:19:27,240
or hyperbolic trigonometry.

1586
01:19:27,240 --> 01:19:29,240
It's a little exercise.

1587
01:19:29,240 --> 01:19:31,240
It's a nice little exercise

1588
01:19:31,240 --> 01:19:36,240
to use the hyperbolic trigonometry

1589
01:19:36,240 --> 01:19:40,240
to compute the compounding

1590
01:19:40,240 --> 01:19:42,240
of two Lorentz transformations.

1591
01:19:42,240 --> 01:19:45,240
If frame two is moving relative

1592
01:19:45,240 --> 01:19:48,240
to frame one with velocity v,

1593
01:19:48,240 --> 01:19:50,240
and frame three is moving relative

1594
01:19:50,240 --> 01:19:52,240
to two with velocity v prime,

1595
01:19:52,240 --> 01:19:55,240
how is three moving relative to one?

1596
01:19:55,240 --> 01:19:57,240
The answer is very simple

1597
01:19:57,240 --> 01:19:59,240
in terms of hyperbolic angles.

1598
01:19:59,240 --> 01:20:02,240
You add the hyperbolic angles.

1599
01:20:02,240 --> 01:20:03,240
Not the velocities,

1600
01:20:03,240 --> 01:20:05,240
but the hyperbolic angles.

1601
01:20:05,240 --> 01:20:09,240
The hyperbolic angle of three moving relative to one

1602
01:20:09,240 --> 01:20:13,240
is the hyperbolic angle of three moving relative to two

1603
01:20:13,240 --> 01:20:16,240
plus two moving relative to one.

1604
01:20:16,240 --> 01:20:18,240
And then you use a bit of trigonometry

1605
01:20:18,240 --> 01:20:20,240
or hyperbolic trigonometry

1606
01:20:20,240 --> 01:20:24,240
to figure out how you do

1607
01:20:24,240 --> 01:20:27,240
the cinches and coshes

1608
01:20:27,240 --> 01:20:30,240
of the sum of two hyperbolic angles.

1609
01:20:30,240 --> 01:20:32,240
Very straightforward.

1610
01:20:32,240 --> 01:20:34,240
And I'll leave it as an exercise

1611
01:20:34,240 --> 01:20:36,240
to see if you can work that out.

1612
01:20:36,240 --> 01:20:38,240
Much easier than anything else.

1613
01:20:38,240 --> 01:20:41,240
Okay, so there we have

1614
01:20:43,240 --> 01:20:46,240
the Lorentz transformations.

1615
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:55,240
Yeah, oh, absolutely, yes.

1616
01:20:55,240 --> 01:20:57,240
That's a good point.

1617
01:20:57,240 --> 01:21:00,240
Yeah, when we, that's right.

1618
01:21:00,240 --> 01:21:04,240
If we have frame one,

1619
01:21:04,240 --> 01:21:07,240
let's call this x1 and y1,

1620
01:21:07,240 --> 01:21:10,240
x2 and y2,

1621
01:21:10,240 --> 01:21:12,240
and finally x3,

1622
01:21:13,240 --> 01:21:18,240
and y3,

1623
01:21:18,240 --> 01:21:21,240
well, then the angle

1624
01:21:21,240 --> 01:21:23,240
of two, let's call,

1625
01:21:23,240 --> 01:21:25,240
of three relative to one,

1626
01:21:25,240 --> 01:21:28,240
let's call it theta one three,

1627
01:21:28,240 --> 01:21:31,240
is just equal to theta one two

1628
01:21:31,240 --> 01:21:33,240
plus theta two three.

1629
01:21:33,240 --> 01:21:37,240
The angle connecting frame one with frame three

1630
01:21:37,240 --> 01:21:39,240
